While controversial to some, we are putting together the story of a very cool “Hot Rod Miura.” In 1978, a California entrepreneur commissioned, fabricator and racer Arnold Zucchi to repaint his newly purchased Miura P400 to Black. The California Carrozzeria, Zucchi, would slightly flare the rear wheel arches, black out all of the trim and install 285/345 wide 15” BBS Magnesium racing wheels. An aggressive and menacing “Hot Rod” was born. A few weeks ago we sent our friend and expert, Chip Davis, to inspect this unique Miura. He was completely shocked at its originality and complete matching numbers, engine and every single body panel. Very excited to have this super cool Miura join us in Miami very soon! Thank you so much to @stephenselzler for putting these artistic teasers together! #miura #hotrod #lamborghini #california #paintitblack

When I walked in to interview @johntemerian, founder and President of @wearecurated, I have to admit that I had a pre-conceived notion about him.

I had only met him two or three times socially and noticed he was a friendly, humble, and overall nice guy.

What I knew about him was that his grandfather and father were both in the luxury sports car industry and upon entering his showroom, I saw what looked like $50M + worth of vintage supercars in a huge building in primely located, mid-town Miami.

I'm not usually one to form an opinion about a person based on appearances alone. However, I'm a little ashamed to admit, I thought there was an element of things being handed to John.

I COULDN'T HAVE BEEN MORE WRONG...

Stay tuned for the full video on RISE Podcast, coming soon. You won't want to miss this one.

From Washing Cars At 9 Years Old to Leading the Vintage Supercar World | John Temerian | RISE, E.13

The day is finally here! RISE Podcast with @johntemerian of @wearecurated is finally live!

It’s no wonder why John is the leading authority in the vintage supercar industry, but until this interview, very few people knew the extreme difficulties he went through to achieve this level of success.

John’s story is full of real life lessons on resilience and attitude in the face of seemingly impossible circumstances. Most people would have given up, for John, it wasn’t an option.

The last week was one of the most incredible automotive experiences of my life. We joined @lamborghini for the Giro Polo Storico celebrating the 60th Anniversary of the brand. Dinner with @massimobottura , unveiling of the Van Halen Miura and driving the most incredible roads of Northern Italy. An overwhelming sensory experience. 

The future of Polo Storico will honor and involve important former factory employees, including my fathers close friend for many years, Ingrid Puschi. Ingrid was first interviewed by Ferruccio Lamborghini in 1967, and remained the factory secretary, amongst many other roles, for over 30 years. Ingrid and the others will be integral to the growing factory archives, and continued preservation and certification by Polo Storico. 

Thank you to the incredible team at Lamborghini Polo Storico for the greatest hospitality, their integrity and heart. 

I am overfilled with passion, great pasta and the best Supercars in the world. @jordiricart @wearecurated #lamborghini #countach #miura #diablo #wearecurated #polostorico @hershel_zelcer_

In 1996, my father sold a Super Fly Yellow on Snowcorn Diablo Roadster to a local Palm Beach collector. Accented with Yellow piping and chrome wheels. It was the first Diablo I ever drove (at 15 years old.) I fell in love. He serviced it for many years, and I have many memories of this car. We recently purchased this 1997 Diablo Roadster in the matching spec. I didn’t realize until researching its history, only 9 Diablo Roadsters were produced for North America in Yellow on Snowcorn. This one brings back so many memories. Over the last few months, these rare V12 Supercars have sold for record breaking numbers at auctions including, BringATrailer. Excited to see they are slowly getting their deserved credit! This 8,000 mile example is coming soon to @wearecurated #lamborghini #diablo (Should we keep the MS racing exhaust or no?)

“Mama always told me not to look into the eyes of the sun…but mama, that's where the fun is…” - Blinded by the Light. In reality, it was my father that always told me to “keep it small,” “don’t shoot for the stars or moon.” Unfortunately, it’s not in his sons DNA. I am in love with the chase, the pursuit of the extraordinary. That being said, it’s not for the faint of heart. Hershel and Sergio from our team spent a few days chasing unicorns in Japan. It’s not all dreams and success. Follow their journey, including a sneak peek inside one of the greatest collections in the world, live Friday at 9am Curated TV YouTube now. #ferrari #lamborghini #unicorns

The most exciting part of my job remains digging through historical documents and learning about the “story” of every car. The provenance of each car is often intertwined with the story of (slightly eccentric) exciting, passionate entrepreneurs, industry titans, celebrities and visionaries. 

The cars of the 1980s and 1990s, were the objects of aspiration. They allowed the young boy or girl to dream big, and create. Manifest, visualize products, services and entire industries. 

Identifying with bold designs, ground breaking technology, and pushing boundaries. The evolution of the Supercar is parallel to the concept of the American Dream. It started with posters, magazines and would lead to video games and social media. 

I believe the future of collecting is filled with outrageous cars like the Koenig Testarossa, Bugatti EB110 SS and Diablo GT. If we look further, there is a generation inspired by modern classics such as the Bugatti Veyron, Ferrari Enzo, Koenigsegg CCX and Lamborghini Murciélago. 

These cars changed the world, they are a part of our culture. I am excited for the future. 

The story of the Donald Weber Koenig Testarossa is just one of many special stories coming this Winter from @wearecurated. 

📸 @jeremycliff #lamborghini #ferrari #testarossa #bugatti #diablogt #countach #murcielago #veyron #koenigsegg

Manual and 1,018hp! The “missing” Koenigsegg CCXR Manual! An enigma in Hypercar circles, the unique specification Koenigsegg CCXR Chassis #065 has been rarely seen over the last 15 years. After chasing the car for many years, we had the opportunity to meet its first and only owner. 

A passionate owner who fell in love with the Swedish brand in 2007, and special ordered this late production CCXR with the “Top Gear” wing deleted, unique color and wheels. A conservative enthusiast who enjoyed using the car for extended night time drives, logging over 8,400 miles during his very discreet ownership. Welcome to Miami, you Swedish supermodel. @wearecurated #koenigsegg #ccxr #unicornspec #savethemanuals photos by @winningauto

Like an artifact from an Indiana Jones epic, feast your eyes on probably the last NOS Lamborghini Miura S/SV exhaust in the world. Still in its original plastic protection, it was purchased by my father in the 1980s from Lamborghini through his friend Ingrid. 

After 55 years of amassing the most incredible Countach, Miura and Diablo parts collection, my dad has allowed me to start selling some items. This exhaust was sold to the steward of an incredibly well preserved Miura S. 

There are many things that will never be sold, to be preserved as part of his legacy and passion. Hopefully, one day cherished by my kids and on display for all enthusiasts to appreciate his love for the brand, @lamborghini. #lamborghini #miura #treasure

The Lamborghini Diablo SE30 represents everything special about the most incredible era at Lamborghini. Launched in September of 1993, the first prototype was unveiled during the factory 30th Anniversary celebration, finished in the shocking Metallic Purple on Bleu Alcantara livery. 

Only 61 VIP customers would choose this color for their new Lamborghini Diablo SE30. While ostentatious, and considered absurd in the 1990s, the shocking Metallic Purple, known as “Lambo Thirty,” has become timeless. 

Since 2016, we have had the opportunity to buy 10 of the “Lambo Thirty” Diablo SE30 examples produced for the world. I have been an outspoken fan and passionate steward of these cars and honored to have sold a total of 19 of the 150 Diablo SE30 examples built. 

I absolutely love these photos from @zachbrehl, it feels as if the “Lambo Thirty” Diablo was made for Miami. #diablose30 #lamborghini #legend

No traction control, no sequential gearbox, no aides or assistance… Pure 585hp screaming from a 6.0 liter V12, perfectly mated to a 5-Speed manual gearbox. The 2000 Lamborghini Diablo GTR represents an epic area of road-going racing cars that were produced by Supercar manufacturers. A pinnacle of the Diablo variants, and limited to only 30 for the world. These incredible period photos feature our Diablo GTR Chassis #19 in its original Arancio Ishtar livery. Captured by motorsports legend, John Brooks. #lamborghini #diablogtr #wearecurated @wearecurated

Looking back at my interview with @johntemerian, founder and CEO of @wearecurated, I’m reminded that as parents, we’re on stage, “performing” our lives to the benefit of our observing children. 

In John’s case, he learned work ethic from his father and grandfather. He also took lessons from his surrounding. 

The lessons I took from John’s story are:

1. Your children are watching, so be the best version of yourself possible.

2. Put your children in nurturing environments so they can become more than the sum of their parents. 

Full video episode on Gary Lipovetsky YouTube channel and audio on RISE Podcast Spotify show.
